unittitle_ssm: Screen Actors Guild, New York Branch Records
abstract_ssm: The Screen Actors' Guild opened its first branch office in New York City in 1938. The minutes of the New York Section of the Screen Actors' Guild reflect the governance and activities of SAG at the local branch level and provide insight into New York SAG's evolving role in the national organization. The minutes also reveal much about SAG's relationship to other unions both in and outside of the entertainment industry.
